              of forgiveneſſe of ſinnes. 
              The forgiveneſſe of ſinnes] This benefit is peculiar to the Church;

The Prophet ſpeaking of Sion, ſaith, The people that dwell therein ſhall have their ſinnes forgiven, Iſai. 32. 24. It is a part of the Covenant that God hath made with his people, that he will forgive their iniquity, &c. Ier. 31. 33. The Saints themſelves, even the beſt upon earth have need of it. If thou Lord ſhouldeſt mark iniquities, Lord, who ſhould ſtand? But there is forgiveneſſe with thee, &c Pſal. 130. 34. See Pſal. 32. 1, 2.
